data.enText: to start or create an organization, a system, etc. that is meant to last for a long time

data.chText: 新条约设立了自由贸易区。
data.enText: The new treaty establishes a free trade zone.
to start having a relationship, especially a formal one, with another person, group or country

data.chText: 这所学校与当地社区建立了良好的关系。
data.enText: The school has established a successful relationship with the local community.
to hold a position for long enough or succeed in sth well enough to make people accept and respect you

data.chText: 那时她作为明星的地位已经确立。
data.enText: By then she was established as a star.

data.chText: 他刚建立起自己的公司，但要站稳脚跟还得花上一段时间。
data.enText: He has just set up his own business but it will take him a while to get established .
to make people accept a belief, claim, custom, etc.

data.chText: 正是这场运动确立了这家报纸的声誉。
data.enText: It was this campaign that established the paper's reputation.

data.chText: 传统是随着时间的推移而得到认可的。

data.enText: to discover or prove the facts of a situation

data.chText: 警方仍在努力确定事故的原因。
data.enText: Police are still trying to establish the cause of the accident.

data.chText: 他们已经证实他是摔伤的。
data.enText: They have established that his injuries were caused by a fall.

data.chText: 我们需要查实枪击发生时她在何处。
data.enText: We need to establish where she was at the time of the shooting.

data.chText: 此后便证实马被注射了麻醉药。
data.enText: It has since been established that the horse was drugged.

ex.chText: 政府计划为当地居民建造新住宅。
ex.enText: The government plans to build new houses for local people.

ex.chText: 他白手起家建立了这家企业。
ex.enText: He built this business from scratch.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，应用范围最广，既可用于表示建造具体有形的建筑，又可用于表示抽象意义上的建立、构建。

ex.chText: 他们造这样一架飞机大约需要3年时间。
ex.enText: It takes them about three years to construct such an plane.

ex.chText: 这幢摩天大楼全部是用水泥和玻璃构筑的。
ex.enText: This skyscraper was constructed entirely of concrete and glass.

synonyms.bx: 强调按照一定设计建造规模较大、结构较复杂的物体，特别指按照图纸构筑某种建筑物。

ex.chText: 该城市将建造一座纪念碑。
ex.enText: A monument will be erected in this town.

synonyms.bx: 指建造高而垂直的建筑物，强调有一定高度。

ex.chText: 两国之间建立了良好的友谊。
ex.enText: A good friendship was established between the two countries.

ex.chText: 这家老字号公司创建于19世纪80年代。
ex.enText: This time-honored company was established in the 1880s.

synonyms.bx: 强调稳固地建成，可指建立国家、政府、学校或商店等，也可指建立信仰、名誉、法律、制度、关系等。

ex.chText: 这座城市由罗马人兴建。
ex.enText: This city was founded by the Romans.

ex.chText: 这些学者创办了一家教育机构。
ex.enText: The scholars have founded an educational institution.

synonyms.bx: 常指通过提供必要的资金创建城市、公司、学校等，含打下基础之意。

ex.chText: 那3个研究生曾想成立自己的出口公司。
ex.enText: Those three postgraduate students wanted to set up their own export business.

ex.chText: 你最好关注一下成立学术组织的新条例。
ex.enText: You'd better pay attention to the new regulations for setting up academic organizations.

synonyms.bx: 侧重指开始着手创建公司、机构、委员会等。

example: base a claim on some observation

tr: establish the validity of something, as by an example, explanation or experiment
example: The experiment demonstrated the instability of the compound
The mathematician showed the validity of the conjecture
Her manager had set her up at the Ritz

tr: set up or lay the groundwork for

example: She set up a literacy program

value.def: If someone establishes something such as an organization, a type of activity, or a set of rules, they create it or introduce it in such a way that it is likely to last for a long time.

example.ex: The UN has established detailed criteria for who should be allowed to vote...
example.tran: 联合国已经制定了有关投票资格的标准细则。

example.ex: The School was established in 1989 by an Italian professor.
example.tran: 这所学院由一名意大利教授于1989年创建。

value.def: If you establish contact with someone, you start to have contact with them. You can also say that two people, groups, or countries establish contact.

example.ex: We had already established contact with the museum...
example.tran: 我们已经和那家博物馆建立了联系。

example.ex: Singapore and South Africa have established diplomatic relations.
example.tran: 新加坡和南非已经建立了外交关系。

value.def: If you establish that something is true, you discover facts that show that it is definitely true.

example.ex: Medical tests established that she was not their own child...
example.tran: 医学化验证实她不是他们的亲骨肉。

example.ex: It will be essential to establish how the money is being spent...
example.tran: 查清楚这笔钱将作何用途至关重要。

example.ex: An autopsy was being done to establish the cause of death...
example.tran: 正在进行尸检以确定死亡原因。

example.ex: It was established that the missile had landed on a test range in Australia.
example.tran: 经证实，那枚导弹已经落在澳大利亚的试验区域内。

example.ex: That link is an established medical fact.
example.tran: 那一关联是已经证实的医学事实。

value.def: If you establish yourself, your reputation, or a good quality that you have, you succeed in doing something, and achieve respect or a secure position as a result of this.

example.ex: This is going to be the show where up-and-coming comedians will establish themselves...
example.tran: 这将是大有前途的喜剧演员们让自己获得认可的节目。

example.ex: He has established himself as a pivotal figure in US politics...
example.tran: 他已经确立了自己在美国政界的核心地位。

example.ex: We shall fight to establish our innocence.
example.tran: 我们应该努力证明自己的清白。

value.tran: 使立足;使被认可;确立(地位)
